1. A wrapper holds a single non-negative integer between 0 and 10.
2. To decide if the wrapped integer is "even-ish": when the integer is 0 the answer is 1; otherwise the answer is whether one less is "odd-ish".
3. To decide if the wrapped integer is "odd-ish": when the integer is 0 the answer is 0; otherwise the answer is whether one less is "even-ish".
